{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011W7eYYifDx4d1XetkVbkoV","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"The task is complete. \n\n## Summary\n\nThe MongoDB replica set in the `mongodb` namespace has been scaled from 3 to 5 members without data loss or loss of availability — using only native StatefulSet + `rs.add()` operations (no operators or CRDs).\n\n**What I did:**\n1. **Discovered the setup** — a 3-member replica set (`mongodb-replica` StatefulSet) with keyfile internal auth + SCRAM. The admin credentials were in the `admin-user-password` secret; the username (`admin-user`, not `admin`) I recovered from the mongod startup logs.\n2. **Recorded a data marker** in the `appdata` database to later prove no data loss.\n3. **Scaled the StatefulSet** to 5 replicas (`kubectl scale`), which provisioned `mongodb-replica-3` and `-4` with their own persistent volumes. The existing 3 members stayed up the whole time (availability preserved).\n4. **Added the new members** to the replica set config via `rs.add(...)` from the primary, using their stable headless-service DNS names.\n5. **Waited for sync** — both new members transitioned `STARTUP2 → SECONDARY`.\n\n**Final verified state:**\n- 5 healthy members: 1 PRIMARY + 4 SECONDARY, all voting (`votes=1`).\n- Marker document successfully replicated to the new `mongodb-replica-4` (count = 1) → no data loss.\n- Replica set config shows `members: 5`, `rs.status().ok = 1`, and the primary never changed during the operation → no availability loss."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":588,"cache_read_input_tokens":43128,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":588},"output_tokens":1,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"1be42b30-7f59-4dde-94b7-d6fb8654e30